dcterms:description: The Adult dataset originates from the 1994 Census database, consisting of 14 attributes and 48,842 instances. The class label indicates whether an individual has an income greater than 50,000 USD/year.

dcterms:description: The Give Me Some Credit (GMC) dataset is a credit scoring dataset, consisting of 150,000 observations and 11 features. The class label indicates if the corresponding individual will experience financial distress within the next two years.
dcterms:title: Give Me Some Credit (GMC) Dataset

dcterms:description: The COMPAS dataset contains data for more than 10,000 criminal defendants in Florida. It is used by the jurisdiction to score defendants' likelihood of re-offending. The class label indicates if the corresponding defendant is high or low risk for recidivism.
dcterms:title: COMPAS Dataset
